Thus, the damage threshold fluence Fth scales with a power law τ(m−1)/m. For m = 1 (linear absorption) the threshold is independent of the pulse duration (consistent with the results gained for metals in the frame of the TTM [37], see Sect. 3.2.1). This result is also in line with the above result for pure AI, which is also based on a cascade of linear absorption processes. It is interesting to note at this point that pure two-photon absorption (m = 2) also leads to the characteristic τ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
